# Rails Bundler Environment

When running Rails, Rake, or Bundler commands in this project, clear Cursor's
temporary Bundler environment first:

```shell
env -u BUNDLE_PATH -u GEM_SPEC_CACHE bundle exec rails test
env -u BUNDLE_PATH -u GEM_SPEC_CACHE bundle exec rails runner '...'
```

Do this whenever a command would otherwise use `bin/rails`, `bundle exec rails`,
`rails`, `rake`, or `bundle exec rake`.

Why: Cursor may inject `BUNDLE_PATH` pointing at a sandbox cache that does not
contain this app's gems, causing `Bundler::GemNotFound` even though the user's
local environment is correctly installed.
